==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quinate
<hw>Qui"nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>quini</ets>
five each.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Growing in sets of five; --
said especially of leaves composed of five leaflets set at the end of a
common petiole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quinate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Quinate
<hw>Qui"nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
salt of quinic acid.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>kinate</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quinazol</ent>⟦br⟧
